quran[23]{c,v,t}:
  33,60,"If the hypocrites and those in whose hearts is a disease and those who spread rumours and trouble in Madinah desist not, We shall certainly urge you on against them. And then they shall not be your neighbours therein but for a little while"
  33,61,"Accursed, they will be seized and slain wherever found"
  33,62,That was the way Allah dealt with those who have gone before. And you will find no change in Allah's way
  33,63,"People ask you about the Hour (the time when the present world will end and the Hereafter begin). Say, \"Information about it is only with Allah. And what do you know, the Hour may be nigh"
  33,64,Allah has indeed cursed the suppressors of Truth and prepared for them a burning Fire
  33,65,They will abide therein forever. They will find neither a wali nor anyone to help
  33,66,"That day when their faces are turned about in the Fire, they will say, \"Woe to us! Would that we had obeyed Allah and obeyed the Messenger"
  33,67,"And they will say, \"Our Lord! We only obeyed our bosses and our seniors. And they led us astray from the right path"
  33,68,Our Lord! Give them a double punishment and give them a severe curse
  33,69,"O you who believe! Be not like those who offended Moses, but Allah cleared him of what they said. And he had an honourable standing with Allah"
  33,70,O you who believe! Fear Allah and speak in appropriate and straight (unambiguous and to the point) words
  33,71,"He (Allah) will improve your deeds for you, and forgive you your sins. And whoever obeys Allah and His Messenger, he/she does certainly achieve a great success"
  33,72,"We did indeed offer the trust to the heavens and the earth and the mountains, but they were unwilling to bear its burden and were apprehensive of it. And man bore that burden! He has indeed been unjust and ignorant"
  33,73,"That Allah may punish the hypocrites, men and women, and the polytheists, men and women. And Allah will turn mercifully to the believing men and the believing women. And Allah is Forgiving, Merciful"
  34,1,"Praise to Allah! To Him belongs whatsoever is in the heavens and whatsoever is in the earth. And to Him belongs praise in the Hereafter! And He is the One wise, aware"
  34,2,"He knows what goes down into the earth and what comes out of it, and what comes down from the heavens and what goes up there. And He is the Merciful, the Forgiving"
  34,3,"And those who suppress the Truth say, \"The Hour (the time when the present world will end and the Hereafter begin) is not going to come to us ever.\" Say, \"Yes, by my Lord, the Knower of the unseen! It is certainly going to come to you.\" No mass (weight) particle is hidden from Him, either in the heavens or in the earth. And nor is there anything less than that nor greater, but clearly recorded"
  34,4,(The Hour is indeed going to come) in order that He (Allah) may reward those who believe and do good deeds. For them there is forgiveness and a noble provision
  34,5,"And for those who strive hard to defeat the purpose of Our Messages, there is punishment of a painful scourge"
  34,6,"And those who have been given knowledge see that what is revealed to you from your Lord is the Truth, and that it guides towards the path of the Omnipotent, the Praised One"
  34,7,"And those who suppress the Truth say, \"Shall we show you a man who informs you that, when you are completely shred into tiny pieces, you will even then be created anew"
  34,8,"Has he forged a lie against Allah or has he gone mad?\" Nay! Those who believe not in the Hereafter are suffering a far-reaching delusion"
  34,9,"See they not what is before them and what is behind them of the heaven and the earth? If We so will, We can cause the earth to swallow them or bring down upon them a chunk of the heavens. There is indeed a sign in this for every obedient human turning in repentance to Allah"